# isNotEqual(to:)

**Instance Method**

Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the receiver is not equal to another given object.

## Declaration

```swift
func isNotEqual(to object: Any?) -> Bool
```

## Parameters

- **object**: The object with which to compare the receiver.

## Return Value

[doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/YES] if the receiver is not equal to `object`, otherwise [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NO].

## Discussion

Currently, [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NSObject-swift.class/isNotEqual(to:)] messages are never sent to any object from within Cocoa itself.

The default implementation for this method provided by `NSObject` method returns [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/YES] if an `isEqual:` message sent to the same object would return [doc://com.apple.objectivec/documentation/ObjectiveC/NO].
